# Direct Execution On Request

- If the user explicitly asks to fix or implement something, do the work directly instead of suggesting `/create-rule`, offering optional next steps, or explaining what could be done first.
- Prefer concise status updates while working and keep explanatory text secondary to execution.
- When a user asks to "do it", treat that as authorization to make the requested code or configuration change immediately.
- Only pause to ask a question when a real blocker exists or the request is ambiguous enough that implementation would be unsafe.
